content.raw:
This prevents the node from crashing for me:

```
diff -r f23104a241cc subt_ros/src/SubtRosRelay.cc
--- a/subt_ros/src/SubtRosRelay.cc      Wed Jul 24 13:08:38 2019 -0700
+++ b/subt_ros/src/SubtRosRelay.cc      Wed Jul 24 15:09:19 2019 -0700
@@ -242,6 +242,10 @@
   _res.success = this->node.Request("/subt/pose_from_artifact_origin",
       req, timeout, rep, result);
 
+  // Request failed, ignore response
+  if (!result)
+    return result;
+
   // Construct the ROS response
   _res.pose.pose.position.x = rep.position().x();
   _res.pose.pose.position.y = rep.position().y();
```

The problem is that the ign-transport response is empty when result is false and we try to get `data(0)`. Interesting that you get a fatal error + exception when I just get a crash.
content.html:

diff -r f23104a241cc subt_ros/src/SubtRosRelay.cc
--- a/subt_ros/src/SubtRosRelay.cc      Wed Jul 24 13:08:38 2019 -0700
+++ b/subt_ros/src/SubtRosRelay.cc      Wed Jul 24 15:09:19 2019 -0700
@@ -242,6 +242,10 @@
   _res.success = this->node.Request("/subt/pose_from_artifact_origin",
       req, timeout, rep, result);

+  // Request failed, ignore response
+  if (!result)
+    return result;
+
   // Construct the ROS response
   _res.pose.pose.position.x = rep.position().x();
   _res.pose.pose.position.y = rep.position().y();

The problem is that the ign-transport response is empty when result is false and we try to get data(0). Interesting that you get a fatal error + exception when I just get a crash.
